lass=3D"text-4xl font-bold" id=3D"overview" data-id=3D"overview">Overview</=
h2><a class=3D"absolute mt-20 opacity-0" id=3D"overview" data-id=3D"hab_ove=
rview"></a><br><p class=3D"font-normal ">Using Workflow Studio, you can bui=
ld no-code workflows to automate your back-office business processes. Gener=
ate notifications, update data, and share information with the right people=
 at just the right time=E2=80=94and do it all automatically. With workflows=
, you can eliminate the busy work of running your business to keep people f=
ocused on what really matters.</p><br><a class=3D"absolute opacity-0 scroll=
-mt-40" id=3D"examples" data-id=3D"hat_examples"></a><h2 class=3D"text-4xl =
font-bold" id=3D"examples" data-id=3D"examples">Examples</h2><a class=3D"ab=
solute mt-20 opacity-0" id=3D"examples" data-id=3D"hab_examples"></a><br><p=
 class=3D"font-normal ">Frequent, repetitive processes are great candidates=
 to be automated with custom workflows. Here are just a few examples.</p><b=
r><h3 class=3D"text-3xl font-bold" id=3D"hrpeople-ops" data-id=3D"hrpeople-=
ops">HR/People Ops</h3><br><ul class=3D"list-disc pl-8"><li class=3D"items-=
start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">Automate the onboarding checklist for new =
hires during their first week:</p><ul class=3D"list-disc pl-8"><li class=3D=
"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">Send informational and policy email=
s.</p></li><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">Schedule onb=
oarding meetings and meet-and-greets.</p></li><li class=3D"items-start"><p =
class=3D"font-normal ">Send a survey asking for feedback on the company onb=
oarding process.</p></li></ul></li><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"fo=
nt-normal ">Celebrate special occasions by sending customized Slack notific=
ations for employee birthdays and anniversaries.</p></li><li class=3D"items=
-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">On a schedule (for example, every Monday =
at 9 AM), query all the employees&nbsp; who have a probation end date appro=
aching and send their manager individual reminder emails.</p></li></ul><br>=
<h3 class=3D"text-3xl font-bold" id=3D"it" data-id=3D"it">IT</h3><br><ul cl=
ass=3D"list-disc pl-8"><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">=
When a device=E2=80=99s operating system is out of date, create a task and =
send an email requesting the employee to complete the update while also cop=
ying their manager.</p></li><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-norm=
al ">Complete device wellness checks based on device age, RAM usage, free d=
isk space, and threat detection activity. Notify the device owner when prob=
lems arise and assign tasks to IT staff to remedy the issues.</p></li></ul>=
<br><h3 class=3D"text-3xl font-bold" id=3D"finance" data-id=3D"finance">Fin=
ance</h3><br><ul class=3D"list-disc pl-8"><li class=3D"items-start"><p clas=
s=3D"font-normal ">Trigger notifications for any compensation change greate=
r than $10,000.</p></li><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal "=
>Send important alerts to payroll admins so they can stay on top of your co=
mpany=E2=80=99s payroll, such as when a pay run is approved, when it=E2=80=
=99s not auto-approved as expected, or when an off-cycle pay run occurs.</p=
></li></ul><br><h3 class=3D"text-3xl font-bold" id=3D"sales" data-id=3D"sal=
es">Sales</h3><br><ul class=3D"list-disc pl-8"><li class=3D"items-start"><p=
 class=3D"font-normal ">When a sales opportunity is marked as closed/won, s=
end a Slack message to a channel and include the dollar amount of the sale =
in the message.</p></li><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal "=
>Send an email with a weekly summary of closed/won opportunities.</p></li><=
/ul><br><h3 class=3D"text-3xl font-bold" id=3D"recruiting" data-id=3D"recru=
iting">Recruiting</h3><br><ul class=3D"list-disc pl-8"><li class=3D"items-s=
tart"><p class=3D"font-normal ">Notify the recruiting team when a new refer=
ral comes in.</p></li><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">W=
hen an offer letter has been sent to a candidate, create a task for a candi=
date=E2=80=99s interviewers to remind them to send a note of congrats to th=
e candidate.&nbsp;</p></li></ul><br><h3 class=3D"text-3xl font-bold" id=3D"=
legal--compliance" data-id=3D"legal--compliance">Legal &amp; Compliance</h3=
><br><ul class=3D"list-disc pl-8"><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"fon=
t-normal ">When someone updates their address in Rippling and their home st=
ate has changed, take the following actions:</p><ul class=3D"list-disc pl-8=
"><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">Assign a task for the=
m to review the certification requirements in their state.</p></li><li clas=
s=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">Send a form where they can uplo=
ad a screenshot of their new license.</p></li><li class=3D"items-start"><p =
class=3D"font-normal ">Message the employee=E2=80=99s manager on Teams so t=
hey can follow up with the employee as needed.</p></li></ul></li><li class=
=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">When an employee's license is ap=
proaching expiration, initiate a task for them to renew.</p></li></ul><br><=
p class=3D"font-normal ">For more information about the available workflow =
triggers and actions, see our <a class=3D"font-normal text-blue-600 hover:c=
ursor-pointer" href=3D"https://help.rippling.com/article?articleId=3D515426=
255495">overview of workflow triggers</a> and <a class=3D"font-normal text-=
blue-600 hover:cursor-pointer" href=3D"https://help.rippling.com/article?ar=
ticleId=3D663137955388">overview of workflow actions</a>.</p><br><a class=
=3D"absolute opacity-0 scroll-mt-40" id=3D"components-of-a-workflow" data-i=
d=3D"hat_components-of-a-workflow"></a><h2 class=3D"text-4xl font-bold" id=
=3D"components-of-a-workflow" data-id=3D"components-of-a-workflow">Componen=
ts of a workflow</h2><a class=3D"absolute mt-20 opacity-0" id=3D"components=
-of-a-workflow" data-id=3D"hab_components-of-a-workflow"></a><br><p class=
=3D"font-normal ">A workflow has three components:</p><br><ul class=3D"list=
-disc pl-8"><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal "><b>Trigger<=
/b>: The trigger initiates the workflow. Triggers can be a specific date/ti=
me, a piece of information changing, or someone clicking a button. Each wor=
kflow has a single trigger.</p></li><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"f=
ont-normal "><b>Actions</b>: Actions are the operations executed by the wor=
kflow, such as sending an email or Slack message, updating some data in Rip=
pling, or calling an API. Each workflow can have multiple actions.</p></li>=
<li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal "><b>Logic</b> (optional)=
: You can optionally add logic that determines when or how an action runs. =
For example, take an action only if a field is over a certain value. If you=
r workflow has several paths, the logic determines which path to take on ea=
ch run.</p></li></ul><br><a class=3D"absolute opacity-0 scroll-mt-40" id=3D=
"get-started-building-workflows-in-workflow-studio" data-id=3D"hat_get-star=
ted-building-workflows-in-workflow-studio"></a><h2 class=3D"text-4xl font-b=
old" id=3D"get-started-building-workflows-in-workflow-studio" data-id=3D"ge=
t-started-building-workflows-in-workflow-studio">Get started building workf=
lows in Workflow Studio</h2><a class=3D"absolute mt-20 opacity-0" id=3D"get=
-started-building-workflows-in-workflow-studio" data-id=3D"hab_get-started-=
